article.headline: W. Illinois 51, S. Utah 48
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Troy Okeson hit a 3-pointer with five-seconds remaining to lift Western Illinois to a 51-48 win over Southern Utah on Saturday. The Thunderbirds had one final chance to tie the game, but Nurudeen Adepoju missed a 3-point shot as time expired. Western Illinois (7-22, 3-11 Mid-Continent) trailed by as many as nine points in the first half. They cut it to 32-29 at halftime and completed the rally to take a 39-37 lead on Xavier Jackson's layup with 12:45 left in the game. The Leathernecks did not trail the rest of the way. Southern Utah tied it at 48 with 1:32 left on a layup by Swaney Cooper and, after the teams swapped turnovers, setting the stage for Okeson's game-winner. Jerryck Owens-Murrey scored 17 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead the Leathernecks. Okeson finished with 12 points, all coming from four 3-pointers. Tate Sorenson and Cooper scored 10 points apiece for Southern Utah (16-13, 6-8 Mid-Continent). The Thunderbirds shot just 32 percent in the second half on 7-of-22 shooting, while Western Illinois shot 40 percent, including going 4-for-10 from 3-point range.
